Derrick, thank you.  It is nice to know that the generation of young people coming into adulthood today have folks such as you amongst their ranks. <br>
 I didn't want anything from my gov't.  Didn't expect anything from my gov't except for the G.I. Bill, maybe. <br>
 But I was raised in an environment and a culture that said that the young men entered the service as &quot;payment for the freedoms&quot;  that we all enjoy.  I'm not saying it is correct or justifing that statement. It just &quot;was&quot;.  I guess that I expected some kind of recognition from Americans for paying that price and doing my duty.<br>
  That is what &quot;we vets&quot;  look for most of all.  The recognition, unasked for and freely given from folks such as you.  <br>
So from a vet of the 1st Cav.  3/18th Arty who did two tours; Thank you.
